#: ../../../library/tkinter.rst:802
msgid "The window manager"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.rst:806
msgid ""
"In Tk, there is a utility command, ``wm``, for interacting with the window "
"manager.  Options to the ``wm`` command allow you to control things like "
"titles, placement, icon bitmaps, and the like.  In :mod:`!tkinter`, these "
"commands have been implemented as methods on the :class:`Wm` class.  "
"Toplevel widgets are subclassed from the :class:`Wm` class, and so can call "
"the :class:`Wm` methods directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../library/tkinter.rst:813
msgid ""
"To get at the toplevel window that contains a given widget, you can often "
"just refer to the widget's :attr:`~Tk.master`. Of course if the widget has "
"been packed inside of a frame, the :attr:`!master` won't represent a "
"toplevel window. To get at the toplevel window that contains an arbitrary "
"widget, you can call the :meth:`~Misc.winfo_toplevel` method. There is also "
"a :meth:`!_root` method; it begins with an underscore to denote the fact "
"that this function is part of the implementation, and not an interface to Tk "
"functionality. It returns the application's root window rather than the "
"nearest enclosing toplevel."
msgstr ""

